  <li><strong>Recognize Méthode Saignée vs. Direct Press Quality Markers</strong> - Saignée rosés (bled from red wine production) often show more concentration and complexity but can lack the elegant restraint of direct press rosés. Direct press rosés typically offer purer fruit expression and better balance. Look for producer notes about method - serious rosé producers who use dedicated direct press methods often create superior, more food-friendly wines.</li>
